<HEADLINE> Contacts Underway with U.S. to Push Forward Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) Yasser Arafat said contacts are going on with the
United States to push forward the Middle East peace process and
implement the signed accords.
</P>
<P>
In a press conference upon his arrival from a tour of Russia
and Egypt, Arafat described his talks with Egyptian President
Hosni Mubarak as "positive and constructive."
</P>
<P>
Mubarak showed, as usual, readiness to play a role in
protecting the peace process and implementing the Sharm El-Sheikh
memo that was signed under Egypt's auspices in early September,
Arafat added.
</P>
<P>
On his talks with the Russian leaders, he said they were
"positive and substantial."
</P>
<P>
He added he had a phone conversation with Russian President
Boris Yeltsin, who is being treated in a hospital, for 45 minutes
to apprise him of the developments in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Arafat condemned the Israeli settlement activities
as "illegal acts that undermine the peace process, a fact that was
admitted to by the United States, Russia, the European Union and
the Arab states." 
</P>
</TEXT>
