<HEADLINE> British PM On Beef Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 1 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony
Blair said his Government is "101 percent behind" the beef
industry's bid to restore export markets after the BSE crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister told a Downing Street meeting of industry
leaders Wednesday that getting the EU beef ban lifted is only the
first step on the road to restoring a market once worth 350
million pounds.
</P>
<P>
The meeting came less than 24 hours after Agriculture Minister
Nick Brown declared that the domestic ban on sales of beef-on-the
bone would be lifted on December 17.
</P>
<P>
"This lifting of the ban has been long awaited and I am
delighted that it can now go ahead," he said. "The announcement
will bring a welcome boost to the beef industry in what continue
to be difficult times."
</P>
<P>
Supermarket giant Safeway is reported putting beef-on-the-bone
on sale in at least one supermarket and plans to sell the banned
meat in other stores later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
