<HEADLINE> 2400 Aids Cases Reported in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Greece has a total number of 2,
400 HIV infected patients, Greece's Deputy Health and Welfare
Minister Theodoros Kotsonis said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference on the occasion of World Day
Against AIDS, he said that of the 2,400, 35 were children.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, figures presented by the University of Athens place
Greece around 10th of European countries in terms of the number of
new AIDS cases.
</P>
<P>
Professor Angelos Hatzakis of the Athens University said that
intravenous drug users were most likely to contract AIDS, followed
by heterosexuals, and homosexual activity came further down the
list.
</P>
<P>
In Greece, the first AIDS case was reported in 1981.
</P>
<P>
HIV infection could significantly increase in the country due
to the growing number of drug users and the influx and mobility of
illegal immigrants and prostitutes from the Eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
In efforts to raise public awareness about AIDS and to reach
out to high-risk groups, various state-supported and private non-
governmental organizations around the country provide social and
psychological support.
</P>
<P>
Under the framework of a nationwide AIDS awareness campaign,
there is a free telephone helpline in Athens and the northern
Greek city of Thessaloniki. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
