<HEADLINE> Aftershocks Continue to Shake Turkish Disaster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- An aftershock shook Turkish
disaster area in the wake of the 7.2-magnitude earthquake which
devastated Duzce county of the Bolu province on November 12.
</P>
<P>
Officials at Bogazici University Randilli Observatory
Seismology Institute said an aftershock measuring 2.9 on
the Richter Scale was recorded in Akcakoca county of Bolu
province early on Wednesday, Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a mild tremor, measuring 3.4 on the Richter scale,
shook another disaster area Karliova.
</P>
<P>
On August 17, a 7.4-magnitude quake hit western Turkey,
killing at least 17,000 people. It was followed by the
7.2-magnitude tremor, in which several hundred people
died. 
</P>
</TEXT>
