<HEADLINE> S.Africa Describes AIDS as New Millenium's Big </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 1 (Xinhua) -- There was little doubt
that the AIDS crisis was the single greatest concern in the new
millennium, South African acting president Mangosuthu Buthelezi
said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Delivering the keynote address at the World AIDS Day
partnership festival, Buthelezi said President Thabo Mbeki would
on his return from Tanzania would announce the establishment of a
national AIDS council, recently approved by the cabinet, to lead
the national AIDS program.
</P>
<P>
