to Tanzania to attend the Burundi peace summit, Buthelezi said.
</P>
<P>
In his speech Buthelezi said that the solution for the AIDS
problem was not one that could come from government or political
leaders alone. It was a very real, threatening disease that had to
be beaten.
</P>
<P>
Buthelezi condemned those who intentionally or ignorantly
spread the disease. "There is nothing more repulsive or abominable
than a person who intentionally spreads AIDS, out of revenge,
selfishness or total disrespect, " he added.  
