<HEADLINE> S. African Exports Rocket to Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 1 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's export has
shot up to a historic high of 14.946 billion rand (2.491 billion
U.S. dollars) in October, with a 911-million-rand (152 million
U.S. dollars) trade surplus.
</P>
<P>
Import has also staged a substantial recovery compared with
previous months, South African Standard Bank said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Imports in October amounted to 14.034 billion rand (2.3 billion
dollars), the highest level so far this year and 2.237 billion
rand above the monthly average for the year through to September.
</P>
<P>
The rise in imports was largely attributed to increased
machinery and mineral product imports. The rise in machinery
imports suggested improved business confidence, while the
continued rise in global crude oil prices was having a material
impact on the import bill. 
</P>
