<HEADLINE> Maintaining China's Social Stability Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Maintaining China's social
stability and creating a favorable social environment to push
forward the country's economy, reform and opening-up will be the
main tasks for the country's political and law departments next
year.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the work of 1999, Luo Guan, Secretary of the Central
Political Science and Law Committee, said at a national political
and law conference which opened today that the political and law
departments have maintained social stability, ensured the safety
of the 50th anniversary of the founding of New China, and created
a positive social environment for the return of Macao this year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the public security departments had
arrested over 230,000 criminals at large by the end of October,
uncovered a large number of serious crimes, and also made
substantial progress in the fight against smuggling, theft, and
car theft.
</P>
<P>
Regarding major tasks for next year, Luo urged departments of
politics and law to intensify the anti-terrorism struggle,
continue the fight against the Falun Gong cult and all other kinds
of cults, create favorable conditions for the reform of State-
owned enterprises and strengthen the supervision of politics and
law department members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
