<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-01 16:21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cypriot Postal Service Department Hooked to Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Cypriot government has
decided to convert the Postal Service Department into a public
company in tandem with more liberalized market.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken by the Council of Ministers in its
meeting Tuesday under President Glafcos Clerides,the Cyprus News
Agency (CNA) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An official announcement said that the state will be the
company's sole shareholder and its employees will be allowed to
become shareholders if they so wish.
</P>
<P>
The announcement also said that the decision was taken in view
of the "de facto liberalization of the postal services market in
Cyprus as some 30 companies are already operating in the field
gaining a substantial part of the market."
</P>
<P>
The move was taken also with an eye on the liberalization in
the field to be adopted by the European Union by the year 2003,
that will lead to more competition for Cypriot state postal
services.
</P>
<P>
It also cites a study by the Cyprus Development Bank, which
warned that if the Postal Service Department is not made
autonomous, "in a few years the Cyprus post offices will be
converted from profit-making to loss-making." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
