<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CCB Transfers Debt Asset to Cinda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 2 (Xinhua)-- The Shanghai branch of the
China Construction Bank (CCB) signed an agreement today to
transfer its debt asset worth some two billion yuan (nearly 230
million U.S.dollars) to Cinda Asset Management Corporation.
</P>
<P>
One of the country's biggest State-owned commercial banks,
China Construction bank started the debt-equity conversion effort
in Shanghai to manage its non-performing assets.
</P>
<P>
Cinda corporation was the first in China to handle bad loans of
the China Construction Bank. Since then, three more companies have
been set up to manage bad loans of the Bank of China, the
Agricultural Bank of China, and the China Industrial and
Commercial Bank.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai subsidiary bank of CCB now is taking all possible
measures to reduce the bank's asset loss to a minimum, including
debt-to-equity swap and asset reorganization.
</P>
<P>
The specialized commercial firms are a step taken by the
Chinese government to prevent risks in the banking sector brought
on by the increasing number of bad loans to state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The corporations can both handle the banks' bad loans and
reduce their bad assets, thus improving asset quality,
profitability and also reducing operation risks of banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991202.0046 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Writethru: Manila Tightens Security After Attack on Oil Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Following the bombing of an oil
company, the Philippine National Police (PNP) has doubled the
security on all the installations in Metro Manila that provide
vital services such as communications, water, electricity and
gasoline depots.
</P>
<P>
The bombing took place on Thursday morning when three
unidentified heavily armed men attacked a gasoline company in
Metro Manila by spraying it with bullets and firing a rifle
grenade at it.
</P>
<P>
A security guard posted at the Shell House building in Makati
city of Metro Manila was injured when the armed men attacked the
oil company at about 4:30 a.m. local time.
</P>
<P>
The security guard was hit with glass splinters and suffered
injuries in the back. Fortunately, aside from the security guard,
there were no other casualties.
</P>
<P>
The explosion also shattered the glass panels on the second,
third and fourth floors of the building, with the third floor
being heavily damaged.
</P>
<P>
The explosion dug a crater 15 inches in diameter and three
inches deep on the third floor of the said building.
</P>
<P>
Police said a group of eight men and two women flagged down a
mega taxi driven by Elmer Rosalin at about 3:45 a.m. local time in
Quezon City of Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
Immediately thereafter, they took over the wheel and
blindfolded the driver. Then, Rosalin said he heard a loud
explosion followed by successive shots.
</P>
<P>
Rosalin, still blindfolded, was dumped shortly after the
attack. He immediately proceeded to the police to report the
incident.
</P>
<P>
The police said the suspects also strafed with automatic
gunfire a British-owned business establishment in Makati.
</P>
<P>
Responding policemen recovered one empty shell of a rifle
grenade and 11 empty bullet shells in the area.
</P>
<P>
The Alex Boncayao Brigade (ABB) of the rebel New People's Army
(NPA) has assumed responsibility over the bombing, the government
said.
</P>
<P>
Presidential Spokesman Jerry Barican said police authorities
have yet to verify the claim, adding that the ABB may have only
claimed responsibility to convince the public it has the
capability to launch such terrorist attacks against the
government.
</P>
<P>
Barican said President Joseph Estrada has ordered the PNP to go
after and prosecute those responsible for the explosion.
</P>
<P>
The president expressed concern over the incident, noting that
a misfiring of the rifle grenade could have led to greater
casualties since the bombing site is not only a commercial area,
but also a residential one, according to Barican.
</P>
<P>
Police probers were still conducting a thorough investigation
of the case to identify the attackers and their motive in
assaulting the building.
</P>
<P>
PNP chief Panfilo Lacson has given a 48-hour deadline for three
concerned top police officials to arrest the 10 suspects in the
bombing.
</P>
<P>
Police artists have started sketching the suspects' images
based on Rasalin's description of them.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the police offered a 200,000-peso (5000 U.S.
dollars) reward for anyone who could inform the police on the
whereabouts of the suspected members of the NPA-ABB who attacked
the building. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991202.0047 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Auditing Issues of Macao SAR Discussed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Council of the
future Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) held a meeting
here Thursday to discuss the function and organization of the
Commission of Audit of the SAR.
</P>
<P>
Executive Council members discussed the power, organization and
staff employment of the commission. However, some details need
more discussions, according to Tong Chi Kin, spokesman for the
Executive Council.
</P>
<P>
The Commission of Audit shall be responsible for checking the
accounts of the SAR government, ensuring that the SAR's policies
are well carried out and making sure that human and fiscal
resources are effectively used, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tong Chi Kin expressed the belief that the Commission of Audit
will be an organ of high efficiency with simple structure.
</P>
<P>
Like the Commission against Corruption and the customs, the
Commission of Audit will be a new organ of the SAR. It shall
function independently and its director shall be accountable to
the chief executive of the SAR, according the Macao Basic Law.
</P>
</TEXT>
