<HEADLINE> Social Stability Continues as China's Top Priority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, one of China's
top seven policy makers, called on all Party committees and
governments at all levels to spare no effort to maintain social
stability.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the closing ceremony of a two-day political and law
conference, Wei, a member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the ruling Chinese
Communist Party, praised the achievements in politics and the
legal field over the past year, especially the crack-down on
terrorism by overseas and domestic hostile forces and various
criminal activities.
</P>
<P>
Next year will bring the change of a century and is the last
year of China's ninth Five-Year plan period. Therefore, it is of
great importance to ably handle tasks in the political and law
field, Wei said.
</P>
<P>
Though China enjoys economic and social progress, political
stability and national unity, there still exist factors
jeopardizing national safety and social stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to crack down on terrorism by hostile forces at
home and abroad, be on guard against activities of Falun Gong cult
and other sects, and help the majority of Falun Gong practitioners
to mend their ways while attacking illegal activities of key
members, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We should continue the fight against all kinds of criminal and
economic activities with the stress on violent and organized
crimes and major cases," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wei call for effective measures to prevent juvenile delinquency
and create a favorable social environment for the growth of
youngsters.
</P>
<P>
Referring to problems among law enforcement officials, Wei said
that political and law departments should clean their own houses,
be honest, and improve the practice of law enforcement. Those who
have violated the law will be punished according to the law.
</P>
<P>
Luo Gan, a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee, urged all participants to fully understand the
importance of stability and prepare for safe celebrations for
Macao's return to the motherland and in the new year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
