<HEADLINE> HK LegCo Passes Provision of Municipal Services Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) Legislative Council (LegCo) on
Thursday passed the Provision of Municipal Services (
Reorganization) Bill, which provides a legal framework for
delivery of municipal services.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong SAR, said he
was delighted that the bill has been passed.
</P>
<P>
"The new legislation will provide us with the basis on which to
move ahead in reorganizing municipal services. Our objective will
be to improve the provision of municipal services to the public,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Constitutional Affairs Bureau welcomed the
passage of the bill, which marked the beginning of a new era in
the delivery of food and environmental hygiene services under a
revised structure which has pledged to provide more coordinated
and effective services.
</P>
<P>
On culture and leisure services, professional inputs and
community participation would be enhanced and resources would be
better utilized, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the administration was thankful to LegCo
Members for their efforts, adding that about 40 meetings were held
by the Bills Committee in the past six months to study the bill.
</P>
<P>
The bill resumed second reading Wednesday and was passed this
evening after a 14-hour discussion.
</P>
<P>
With the development of representative government in the past
decades, part of the functions of the three-tier constitutional
structure might be overlapped and a reorganization exercise to
streamline the structure is necessary, according to the spokesman.
</P>
</TEXT>
