<HEADLINE> Chinese Universities, Colleges Welcome Return of Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- With the return of Macao
imminent, activities to welcome the event are surging in some
Chinese universities and colleges in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing University, one of the country's most prestigious
institutes of higher education, hundreds of students participated
in a contest themed with Unity, Patriotism and the Future. The
university's activities to welcome Macao's return also include a
singing competition and a long-distance race.
</P>
<P>
People's University of China has hosted a series of lectures
since early November to give students further understanding of
Macao's history, economy and politics.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, students in the university staged a photography
exhibition and aired TV programs this week to highlight Macao's
history, current situation and bright future.
</P>
<P>
Students in Beijing Normal University said that they are
looking forward to Macao's return to the motherland which will
take place on December 20.
</P>
<P>
The university students in Beijing have opened a website for
Internet users to browse their activities commemorating Macao's
return.
</P>
<P>
On the eve of December 19, thousands of students from
universities in Beijing will attend the celebration gala at the
Tian'anmen Square to mark the historic event.  
</P>
</TEXT>
