<HEADLINE> Suspect in Crime Spree Seized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese police have seized a
man suspected to have murdered 22 people, wounded six others, and
committed several rapes and robberies in a two-year crime spree.
</P>
<P>
The police apprehended Liu Jun, 28, in the Kaihuashi district
of Taiyuan, capital city of the northern province of Shanxi on
November 30.
</P>
<P>
Liu was said to be connected with 29 criminal cases in eight
cities over a five-province area since 1997, the police reported.
</P>
<P>
The police said Liu, who was born in the city of Tongguan in
northwestern Shaanxi Province, passed himself off as an
electrician repairing indoor heating systems or telephones.
</P>
<P>
The crimes had drawn the attention of the Ministry of Public
Security which sent officers to co-operate with the local police
in the search for Liu.
</P>
<P>
Liu's case is still under investigation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
