<HEADLINE> New Champions Russia Loses to Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 2 (Xinhua) -- New champions Russia ended the
World Cup men's volleyball tournament on a losing note as they
crashed to Spain in five sets on the final day of the competition
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Russians, who have secured top place Wednesday and a berth
in the Sydney Olympics, went down 22-25, 25-18, 25-23, 25-27, 13-
15 in 116 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, Cuba clinched the last ticket available
here for Sydney by beating Italy 25-18, 23-25, 25-23, 25-16 to
join Russia and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The United States downed Canada 25-21, 20-25, 26-24, 25-20 to
finish fourth while Brazil beat hosts Japan 25-16, 23-25, 25-19,
25-16 to come fifth.
</P>
<P>
China, who lost their final battle 22-25, 20-25, 25-19, 23-25
to Argentina, ended up with the last place. 
</P>
