<HEADLINE> State Banquet in Beijing for World Ozone Forum Delegates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Delegates from more than 100
countries and international organizations to an ongoing world
ozone layer meeting tonight attended a banquet hosted by Chinese
Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao.
</P>
<P>
Among those 700 guests were Shafqat Kakakhel, deputy executive
director of the United Nations Environment Program, and Xie
Zhenhua, director of China's State Environmental Protection
Administration.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, known as the 11th Meeting of the Parties to the
Montreal Protocol on Substances that Deplete Ozone Layer, is an
annual event to discuss the implementation of international
programs designed to control the production and consumption of
ozone-damaging chemicals.
</P>
<P>
The five-day meeting is scheduled to conclude on Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
