<HEADLINE> Sensex Up Sharply in Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index (Sensex)
Thursday rose by 76.71 points on the Bombay Stock Exchange
following revival of support from speculators as well as fresh
purchases by foreign institutional investors and local funds.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share Sensitive Index ended at 4,691.07 as against
Wednesday's close of 4,614.96, netting a rise of 76.71 points or
1.66 percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 Index spurted by 36.54 points to 2,278.97 from
previous close of 2,242.43.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 Index and the Dollex were quoted remarkably up at
528.68 and 202.76 compared with previous close of 521.77 and
200.11, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 Index advanced by 17.47 points to 1,586.96 from
Wednesday's close of 1,569.49. 
</P>
