<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five Killed in Somali Clan Clash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Five gunmen were killed and
at least three others wounded when rival militiamen exchanged
heavy gunfire outside Lego Village, about 40 km northeast of
Ballidogleh airport on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to reports received from eyewitnesses contacted on
the VHF field radios in Lego Village, the contending subclans,
Elay subclan of Rahanwein and Ayr subclan of Habar Gidir, belong
to the supporters of faction leader IIussein Mohamed Aidid.
</P>
<P>
The Elay and Ayr militiamen under the leadership of the
Ballidogleh security commander, Abdukarim Farabadan, have been
defending the only tarmac airport of Ballidgoleh against possible
attacks from the Ethiopian- backed Rahanwein Resistance Army (RRA)
who ousted Hussein Aidid's militiamen out of Baidoa town in June
this year.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the fighting is not stated officially, however
independent sources confirmed that the clashes began after the Ayr
subclan militiamen had disarmed units from the Elay militiamen
whom they allegedly suspected of trying to escape with the weapons
to Bur Hakaba town controlled by the RRA fighters.
</P>
<P>
Elay militiamen annoyed by the disarmament have then attacked
the Ayr militia positions. Independent sources said the Elay
militiamen have been pushed backward with some fatalities. Three
of those wounded during the exchange of fire have been brought to
Mogadishu for treatment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
