<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Exports UP 9.4 Percent in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's exports and
imports were up 9.4 percent and 9.6 percent, respectively, in
September this year, according to the Hong Kong Census and
Statistics Department Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Among the exports, entrepot trade increased by 12.1 percent
than in September 1998, and the regional exports fell by 7.1
percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the first nine months of 1999 with the same 1998
period, Hong Kong's entrepot trade was up 2.4 percent, and the
regional exports was down 9.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Taken together, Hong Kong's total exports increased by 0.7
percent while imports fell by 3.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The change in this regard is due to the price fluctuations in
trade, sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
