<HEADLINE> HK Product Expo to See More Sale: Organizer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The coming 34th Hong Kong
Products Expo (HKPE) will see more sale than the 33rd expo due to
economic recovery in the second half of 1999, said the organizer
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The overall sale of the 1999 expo will increase from last year
's expo thanks to the recovering economy in the second half of the
year and the improving retail market," said President of the
Chinese Manufacturers' Association (CMA) Chan Wing Kee at a press
conference.
</P>
<P>
Chan expected the person times to visit the expo, to be open
from December 11, 1999 to January 2, 2000, will grow by about 33
percent to one million in comparison with the 33rd expo held last
year.
</P>
<P>
All the 650 indoor and outdoor booths of the expo have been
rented out, an increase of 30 percent than the 1998 expo, said
Chan.
</P>
<P>
This reflects manufacturers' confidence in the 1999 expo and
the consumption market, he said.
</P>
<P>
The expo will cover an area of 20,000 square meters, displaying
a wide range of products including textile, clothing, footwear &AMP;
hat, toys, electronic products, electrical appliances and
pharmaceutical products.
</P>
<P>
Celebration for Macao's return to China will be one of the
major programs during the expo.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive of the Macao Special Administrative Region Ho
Hau Wah will visit the expo on December 29, said Chan.
</P>
<P>
The CMA inaugurated the 1st HKPE in 1938 to enhance Hong Kong's
commercial and industrial development, as well as to promote Hong
Kong's external trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
