more difficult to salvage bodies from the water. No matter how
difficult it is, we should try in every possible way to
effectively handle problems arising from the accident."
</P>
<P>
The safety of rescuers will be ensured throughout their work.
Every possible effort will be made to claim bodies and care for
the relatives of the victims, Wu said. Relevant departments should
accelerate the pace of investigation, he added.
</P>
<P>
Wu rushed to Yantai soon after a national conference on
production safety closed Wednesday afternoon. While in Yantai, he
heard reports of rescue operations and extended his regards to
divers, the naval force of the People's Liberation Army, armed
police and medical workers.  
