<HEADLINE> Guangdong and Macao Public Security Destroy Macao Gang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Public security officers in
south China's Guangdong Province and Macao have recently arrested
all seven members of a crime gang in Macao.
</P>
<P>
The efficient information exchange and joint efforts of the
police in the two areas resulted in the October 9 capture of one
of the ringleaders, Che Man Kuong, another five suspects between
October 27 and November 3, and the final gang member on November 7
in Fuqing city in south China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Six of the suspects are from Macao and the seventh is from
central China's Hunan Province. The gang, with another leader Ng
Cheng Weng, has been involved in a series of bank robberies since
1995. Five of their robberies in Macao netted a total 20 million
yuan (2.4 million U. S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The case is under further investigation. 
