saw as endangering the chances of developing countries' getting a
better deal in the new trade round.
</P>
<P>
Many developing countries fear that U.S.- and European-backed
attempts to place labor standard and environmental issues on the
table for the next trade round are aimed at raising new
protectionist barriers to their exports as tariffs and other
restraints come down.
</P>
<P>
Among the concrete issue South Africa and its partners wanted
to address was "the precise working of the rules for anti-dumping
and countervailing duties". 
