<HEADLINE> Compensation for Arab Victims of Terror Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Several Israeli Knesset
(Parliament) Members had successfully sent a bill, calling for
equal compensation for victims of Arab and Jewish terror, through
the first legislation procedure, local newspaper Ha'aretz
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The bill, proposed by lawmaker Husseina Jabarra of Meretz
party, was discussed in Wednesday's Knesset session. Thirty-two
Knesset members voted in favor of sending the bill for first
reading to a committee and fourteen voted against.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper reports, although there are more and
more cases of terror attacks by Jews against Arabs, the current
Compensation Law for Victims of Hostilities still does not
compensate Arab victims of hostile acts motivated by
nationalistic or political reasons.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the bill, said Jabarra, is to give equal
treatment to all victims of terrorism, regardless of their race,
religion and creed.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Finance Minister Nissim Dahan, of the religious Shas
party, said the government had no objection to the bill. 
</P>
</TEXT>
