<HEADLINE> Phone Credit Cards Feature Achievements of the Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- China Telecom Guangdong
Provincial Branch joined hands with Hong Kong Telecom in
publishing two sets of phone credit cards featuring China's
scientific progress throughout Chinese history.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's phone credit cards feature block printing, man-
made satellites, the scientific treatise "Tiangong Kaiwu" by the
Ming dynasty scientist Song Yingxing (1587-?) and the Forbidden
City.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong phone credit cards feature cards reflecting the
application of firearms, Compendium of Materia Medica by Li
Shizhen (1518-1593), the abacus and the voyage of the maritime
explorer Zheng He (1371-1435).
</P>
<P>
The credit phone will enable users to make local, country and
overseas calls.  
