<HEADLINE> Zambian President Appoints 14 District </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba has appointed 14 district administrators to coordinate and
harmonize government functions at district level.
</P>
<P>
There is need to have administrators at district level to
explain and implement government policy at grass root levels, the
president said at a press briefing in Lusaka Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Some provinces are vast and huge and the provincial deputy
ministers are unable to deliver services hence the need for the
appointment of district administrators, Chiluba said.
</P>
<P>
The administrators will help the provincial deputy ministers
and permanent secretaries in their work, he said.
</P>
<P>
The administrators will also coordinate developmental resources
for political and social mobilization, he added.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this month, all the remaining 58 districts will
have their administrators, the president said, promising to
appoint more women as administrators.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba urged all those appointed to take their job seriously
as their performance will make government fail or succeed in
policy implementation at district level. 
</P>
