<HEADLINE> Zambia, Kenya Needs to Cooperate in Tourism: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- There is need for Zambia and
Kenya to cooperate in tourism, a senior Zambian official has said.
</P>
<P>
The two countries would cooperate in hotel standards
inspection, joint marketing and promotion, research and training,
Romance Sampa, Permanent Secretary in charge of tourism, said at a
meeting of the Zambia/Kenya Technical Committee on Tourism and
Wildlife in Lusaka Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Zambian government's policy in the tourism sector has been the
facilitation of private sector investment and the industry has
seen the privatization of all accommodation establishments
previously under state control, Zambia Daily Mail newspaper
Thursday quoted Sampa as saying.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Kenyan Director of Tourism, Clement Mwatsama also said
there is need for private sectors in both Kenya and Zambia to
invest in tourism to strengthen the cooperation between the two
countries. 
</P>
