<HEADLINE> Genghis Khan's Offspring Face New Challenges In the New Millennium (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Baoyin, a 37-year-old herdsman, said that "we need to learn how
to grow crops and develop tourism." It's not easy, but people have
to keep up with the times, he added.
</P>
<P>
Times are changing. Big cities have witnessed rapid growth over
the past few decades. High buildings and advertising signs are
everywhere in Hohhot, capital of the autonomous region and Baotou,
an industrial center in the region's west.
</P>
