<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Exports Grow from January to October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- From January to October 1999,
the Philippines posted an export revenue of 29.016 billion U.S.
dollars, 19 percent higher than the 24.387 billion dollars a year
earlier, the National Statistics Office said in a report Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, for the month of October alone, total
receipts rose by 36 percent to 3.458 billion dollars from 2.542
billion dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
The increase rate of October is the highest figure since the
39.5-percent gain posted in April 1997, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The report showed that for October, manufactured goods went up
by 37.9 percent as sales reached 3.156 billion dollars, up from
2.289 billion a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
This major export group accounted for 91.3 percent of the total
receipts.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, income from agro-based products amounted to 157.16
million dollars or 4.5 percent of the total. Aggregate revenue for
these commodity groups grew by 13 percent from 139.08 million
dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Accounting for 24.7 percent of the aggregate receipt for the
month, the value of exports to the United States was placed at
854.43 million dollars, inching up by 0.9 percent from 846.83
million dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan followed with a 13.8-percent share while the country's
third biggest market, Japan, accounted for 12.8 percent of total
exports for October, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Other top markets for the month were the Netherlands,
Singapore, Britain, Malaysia, Germany and South Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
