<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, December 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Steel production in Latin America is estimated
to total 50 million tons by the end of this year, a 3.1 percent
drop over 1998, a steel institute said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The International Iron and Steel Institute attributed the fall
to the economic recession in the region since last year. (Steel
Production-Latin America)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The International Finance Corporation (IFC)
announced Wednesday that it will invest 14 million U.S. dollars to
finance the construction and operation of a new container and
general cargo terminal at Zhapu Port in Zhejiang Province, eastern
China.
</P>
<P>
The IFC has signed an agreement for an equity investment of 3
million dollars in China Infrastructure Group Holdings PLC (CIGPLC)
and approved loans totaling 11 million dollars to CIG Zhapu
International Terminal Two Company Limited. The new port will be
built adjacent to an existing petrochemical and general cargo
terminal on the northern half of Hangzhou Bay. (IFC-China)
</P>
<P>
