</P>
<P>
SEATTLE -- The European Union (EU) worked toward seeking broad
support during the third ministerial conference of the World Trade
Organization (WTO) on Wednesday in an appeal for a comprehensive
new round of global trade talks.
</P>
<P>
Amid massive street protests against global trade
liberalization, representatives from 135 WTO member countries have
gathered in Seattle in a bid to work out a common ground for the
launch of a new round of global trade negotiations. (EU-WTO)
</P>
<P>
