<HEADLINE> Fiscal Deficit Up 22 Percent in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The fiscal deficit shot up by
22 percent during April-October 1999 touching 577.33 billion
rupees (13.43 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to the Finance Ministry, this represented 72.2
percent of the budgetary target of 799.95 billion rupees (18.6
billion dollars) fixed for the current fiscal.
</P>
<P>
Both the revenue deficit and primary deficit were running at
higher levels, financial officials said.
</P>
<P>
During April-October 1999, the government ran a revenue deficit
of 395.28 billion rupees (9.19 billion dollars), which is almost
73 percent of the amount earmarked in the budget. 
</P>
