<HEADLINE> Anhui Reports Good Autumn Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANHUI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Despite serious drought and
floods that hit Anhui in summer this year, the province reported a
rich autumn harvest of nearly 17.27 million tons of grain, a 2.4
percent decrease from last year.
</P>
<P>
Anhui, a traditional agricultural province, has grown more than
3.4 million ha. of autumn-harvested grain this year, with per-ha
yield exceeding five tons, dropping only 2.9 percent from last
year's figure.
</P>
<P>
Local areas along the Yangtze river have had serious flooding
this year while regions to the north of the Huanhe River have
stricken with drought.  
