<HEADLINE> Philips Sets Up Inductance Rectifier Plant in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Philips has set up an Lighting
Electronics Plant in the city of Xiamen in east China's Fujian
Province to produce inductance rectifiers used in fluorescent
lamps and high-voltage gas lamps.
</P>
<P>
Philips Lighting Electronics Plant (Xiamen) Co. Ltd. will build
their Plant in the district of Huli which will initially cost 4.34
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
