<HEADLINE> Malaysia Urges Refined Regional Security Structure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad Thursday called for the establishment of a
refined all-Asian regional security structure.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir made the call at the opening of the Aerospace and
Maritime International Conference held in conjunction with the
ongoing five-day Langkawi International Maritime and Aerospace
(LIMA) '99 exposition in Malaysia's northern resort island of
Langkawi.
</P>
<P>
"In view of the critical importance of keeping peace and
harmony in this area, I would like to call for a refined regional
security structure that will involve every nation in Asia," he
said in his keynote address at the conference.
</P>
<P>
He said a clear and definite security structure can help save
tremendous resources, minimizing unnecessary duplication and at
the same time fostering closer cooperation among the nations.
</P>
<P>
The LIMA '99 exhibition, opened Wednesday by Mahathir,
attracted some 1,000 local, regional and international companies.
