Hardaway has been sidelined since playing 33 minutes in a 113-
106 loss at Atlanta on November 23. Ironically, the Heat have won
all three games without Hardaway, who is averaging 17.2 points and
7.7 assists in 11 games this season.
</P>
<P>
Hardaway, 33, has had knee trouble throughout his career. Last
season, he was slowed by a hyperextended right knee and had
postseason surgery to repair cartilage damage in his left knee.
Early in his career, he suffered a torn ACL.
</P>
<P>
During the offseason, Hardaway played for Team USA in the
Tournament of the Americas, helping the United States claim an
Olympic berth.
</P>
<P>
The 6-foot Hardaway is in his 11th NBA season and fifth with
the Heat. He has one of the best crossover dribble moves in the
league and owned career averages of 19.4 points and 8.9 assists in
660 games entering this season.
</P>
<P>
The Heat also activated forward Harold Jamison from the injured
list. The undrafted rookie free agent has not played this season.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
