<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Airlines Pilots Refuse to Work Overtime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh Biman, the country's
national airlines, had to cancel five flights on Wednesday as its
pilots refused to fly overtime in addition to their normal duties,
press reports here said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Several international flights while some others were delayed.
</P>
<P>
Domestic flights for Jessore, Sylhet and Khulna were also
canceled.
</P>
<P>
Pilots were quoted as saying they were often forced to take off
without "mandatory rest" of two days beyond their charter of
agreement with the Biman due to shortage of pilots.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh Airlines Pilots Association (BAPA) decided not
to perform any additional duty beyond the contract.
</P>
<P>
Flights were resumed late Wednesday night after a memorandum of
understanding was signed between Biman management and the BAPA.
</P>
