<HEADLINE> China's New Products Welcomed in Central Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- A commercial and trade center
established by a collectively-owned company of southwest China's
Xinjiang Autonomous Region in Alma-ata, capital of Kazakhstan, is
promoting the sale of Chinese new products in Central Asian
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Yalian China Commercial and Trade Center sponsored by the
Urumqi Yalian Trade Co. Ltd with approval from the Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, is the first large
commercial center set up by China in Central Asia.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the center is to create a trade zone in Central
Asia and to provide opportunities for Chinese new products to
enter the Central Asian, Russian and European market, said Li Han,
deputy director of the Xinjiang company.
</P>
<P>
The center covers a floor space of 13,000 square meters and is
mainly engaged in wholesale business. It began business at the end
of 1998.
</P>
<P>
China's VCDs and other electronic appliances enjoy good sales
on the market in Central Asia countries of Kazakhstan, Uzbekistan,
Turkmenistan, Tadzhikistan and Kirghizstan and Russia. 
</P>
