<HEADLINE> Drugs Seized in Tangerang, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian police arrested six
people and seized 68.5 kilograms of marijuana with an estimated
street value of 27.4 million rupiah (3,900 U.S. dollars) in
Tangerang near Jakarta on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Indonesian Observer Thursday, acting on
information provided by local people, police arrested a man
involved in drug dealing and later rounded up five others.
</P>
<P>
An Indonesian psychiatrist said recently that an estimated 1.3
million Indonesians are drug addicts and believed to be spending
about 130 billion rupiah (18.6 million dollars) on drugs a day.
</P>
</TEXT>
