<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Handicapped People Employed in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, December 2 (Xinhua)-- Wang Changming, who has been
blind for years, opened a massage clinic in Changchun two years
ago with financial support from the local government.
</P>
<P>
Sources show that some 115,000 handicapped people in Jilin
Province in northeast China have either established their own
businesses or found jobs in enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Jilin province has been trying to help the handicapped to find
employment in some local enterprises. And the provincial
government has also organized vocational training classes and
adopted preferential policies to encourage the handicapped to
establish their own businesses.
</P>
<P>
The rate of employment of the handicapped in Jilin this year
has increased to about 70 percent from nearly 50 percent in 1987.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
