<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Union Sets Up First Manager Training Center in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The National Economic Research
Institution of Spain (NERIS) and the Tianjin Institute of Finance
and Economics have set up an international training center in
north China's Tianjin to train managing staffs for small and
medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The center offers scientific research, training, and
consultation and services for foreign investors and Chinese firms,
said local officials.
</P>
<P>
The center, financed by the Spanish government, will recruit
its first group of students from May 2000 for one year MBA
programs, said Prof. Marios Nikolinakos, NERIS president.
</P>
<P>
European Union officials in charge of trade affairs in China
said that small and medium-sized enterprises will be the most
competitive enterprises if the agreement on China's accession to
the WTO (World Trade Organization) is reached between the European
Union and China. The establishment of the training center will
also support European enterprises in expanding their businesses.
</P>
<P>
Small and medium-sized enterprises account for more than 90
percent of enterprises in the European Union and China. According
to Chinese economists, these enterprises will not only accelerate
economic growth but will also provide more job opportunities for
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
