<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Killed in New Unrest in Ambon, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- At least three persons were
killed in fresh unrest in Ambon, capital of Indonesia's Maluku
province, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The victims included two civilians and a serviceman from the
army's 12th Engineers' Unit, the Antara News Agency reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the turmoil that occurred in the Ahuru area in Ambon's
Sirimau subdistrict on Wednesday afternoon, five houses were also
burned down.
</P>
<P>
The serviceman was shot by an unidentified person using a
standard army rifle while he was on duty in the Ahuru area.
</P>
<P>
Ambon and its surrounding areas have been ravaged by a series
of communal clashes over the last few months. The worst riots
occurred in the January-March period and claimed hundreds of
lives.
</P>
<P>
President Abdurrahman Wahid last week expressed the hope that
Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri will soon visit Maluku to
solve the problems that have arisen in the riot-torn province.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
