<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expert: World's Largest Underground Funnel in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The largest underground
funnel area in the world is located in Shijiazhuang, capital of
Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The total area of the underground funnel is 50,000 km. Ying
Ruozhi, general engineer at No.2 Reconnaissance Institute of
Hebei Province said that the underground funnel is caused by
excessive use of groundwater. More than ten major underground
funnels have been connected. The water level at the center drops
every year.
</P>
<P>
A main underground funnel at Cangzhou, close to the port city
of Tianjin, has exceeded 10,000 km. Another underground funnel in
southeastern part of Hebei Province has expanded by 305 km each
year and now is about 10,000 km long.
</P>
<P>
North China is one of the most arid regions in the country. The
available water resources in the province of Hebei are no more
than 17 billion cubic meters while the annual water consumption is
20 billion.
</P>
<P>
Ground sinking ranging from 200 to 1,000 millimeters affects an
area of 70,000 meters in Hebei. About 200 ground splits were found
in 35 counties. The deepest ground split had a visible depth of 10
meters.
</P>
<P>
Ying said that water resources in north China will not meet the
demand of social and economic development in the next decade
unless effective measures are taken immediately.
</P>
<P>
A project of diverting water from parts of southern China to
the north is being planned by the central government. Relevant
departments are making preparations to start the project as soon
as possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
