<HEADLINE> Canada Announces Assistance for Fighting AIDS in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Canada will provide 50 million
Canadian dollars (34 million U.S. dollars) to help Africa in its
battle against HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Canadian minister for international cooperation, Maria Minna,
Wednesday announced the new funding in a statement to mark the
World AIDS Day.
</P>
<P>
"HIV/AIDS is killing millions of people," said the minister,
adding that "all countries have a responsibility to aggressively
and unrelentingly attack this disease."
</P>
<P>
The Canadian minister also announced a commitment to host an
international conference on HIV/AIDS prevention in the spring of
the year 2000. 
</P>
