<HEADLINE> Former Soviet High Jump Champion Dies at 40 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, Ukraine, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Former Soviet high jumper
Vladimir Yashchenko has died of cirrhosis of the liver. He was 40.
</P>
<P>
Yashchenko, who held the world indoor and outdoor world records,
died Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Yashchenko set the world indoor record of 2.34 meters at the
1978 European Championships at Milan, Italy, and set the outdoor
mark of 2.35 meters at Tbilisi later that year and won the
Europoean outdoor title at Prague.
</P>
<P>
Yashchenko was injured in 1979 and had to retire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
