<HEADLINE> Steel Production in Latin America Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Steel production in Latin
America is estimated to total 50 million tons by the end of this
year, a 3.1 percent drop over 1998, a steel institute said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The International Iron and Steel Institute attributed the fall
to the economic recession in the region since last year.
</P>
<P>
Steel consumption will decrease by 45 percent in Venezuela at
the end of 1999, followed by Argentina with 35 percent, Peru 24
percent and Chile 16 percent. But the institute predicted that,
with the economic recovery, there will be a greater demand for
steel next year in Latin America. 
</P>
</TEXT>
