<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kanu Voted African Footballer of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian international
Nwankwo Kanu has been voted African Footballer of the Year, it was
announced by the African Football Confederation (CAF) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Arsenal star also won the award in 1996 when he
captained Nigeria to victory at the Atlanta Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Kanu played for Ajax and Inter Milan before joining English
Premiership side Arsenal this year and scored a hat-trick in the
recent 3-2 victory over Chelsea in a London derby.
</P>
<P>
Kanu collected 46 points from the CAF technical and media
committees, two more than Ghana defender Samuel Kuffour, a member
of the Bayern Munich team beaten by Manchester United in the
European Champions League final.
</P>
<P>
Cote d'Ivoire striker Ibrahima Bakayoko came third with 42
points and former winner George Weah of Liberia was fourth.
</P>
</TEXT>
