<HEADLINE> 6 Killed in Train Crash Near Sydney, Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Canberra, December 2 (Xinhua) -- At least six people died when
a commuter train smashed into the back of a train at the foot of
the Blue Mountains west of Sydney in Southeast Australia Thursday,
AAP reported.
</P>
<P>
About 20 people remained trapped in the wreckage and up to 35
were hurt, including 25 with serious injuries, an ambulance
spokesman was quoted as saying.
</P>
