<HEADLINE> Uganda Urges Youths to Fight HIV/AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The official made the appeal at the function organized by the
UAC in the northern district of Masindi on Wednesday to mark the
World AIDS Day, Radio Uganda reported.
</P>
<P>
According to Rwomushana, the function is designed to highlight
the dangers of the pandemic and urge the young people to establish
healthy habits of behavior.
</P>
<P>
He promised to do more to curb the spread of AIDS in the
African country.
</P>
<P>
Uganda is among the few countries in the world where great
progress has been made in the combat against HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
The HIV infection rate in the country has dropped from over 30
percent five years ago to the present level of 12 percent. Among
those aged 15-19, HIV prevalence has declined from 32.2 percent in
1991 to the present 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Although Uganda has achieved a lot in this field, the young
people are still the most vulnerable to the disease, Rwomushana
said.
</P>
<P>
He said the multi-sectoral campaign against AIDS is the right
solution to the problem and the young people should cooperate with
the government and other agencies to help bring down the infection
rate further. 
</P>
</TEXT>
