<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Holds Solemn Funeral for Well-known Sinologist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- France held a Solomon quasi-state
funeral on Wednesday for the well-known Sinologist, life-long
friend of China, writer and former Gaullist minister Alain
Peyrefitte, who died of cancer last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
French President Jacques Chirac, Senate President Christian
Poncelet, former Prime Minister Raymond Barre, former Prime
Minister Alain Juppe and hundreds of other French personalities,
mainly from the Gaullist Rally for the Republic and centrist Union
for French Democracy, as well those from the cultural and press
circles, attended the funeral held at the Invalides military
museum.
</P>
<P>
The square in front of the Saint-Louis Church of Invalides was
covered with wreaths and flowers, and a military honor was given
to Peyrefitte after a religious ceremony in front of the coffin of
the dead which was covered with the tri-color national flag of
France, with the slow and solemn melody of ``March of Funeral'' of
Frederic Chopin in the air.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to France, Wu Jianmin, represented China at
the funeral, standing in the front-line of the attendants.
</P>
<P>
Two French Academicians and close friends of Peyrefitte's, Jean-
Francois Deniau and Jean d'Ormesson, paid homage to the sinologist
in their speeches at the funeral, calling Peyrefitte ``a fighter
of spirit'' and one who sought truth throughout his life.
</P>
<P>
``Under the cover of a political person, we are among those who
have seen a warm-hearted man, a man who sought truth, a
conscientious worker and a man devoted to the good of the public,
'' said Deniau.
</P>
<P>
``He is a man of faith and intelligence, a man of culture and
statesmanship, a man of passion and of reason,'' said d'Ormesson.
</P>
<P>
The funeral ended in the church bell ringing for the dead and
the French national anthem, ``la Marseillaise.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991202.0270 </DOCNO>
