<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama Launches Anti-AIDS Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Panama launched an AIDS
awareness campaign Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the activities marking the World AIDS Day, the health
authorities organized a procession in downtown Panama City,
distributing leaflets with information for prevention of the
disease, calling for "safe sex."
</P>
<P>
Panama's President Mireya Moscos also jointed the activities in
the day.
</P>
<P>
The treatment for one AIDS patient in Panama needs 1,000
dollars per month, President of the Antidrugs Medical Fund Honorio
Bernal said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Health Ministry said 2,820 people have died of the disease
since the first AIDS case occurred in the country in 1984. It
estimated that Panama has some 27,000 carriers of HIV, the virus
that causes AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Panama, with a population of 2.68 million, is one of the Latin
American countries with more AIDS patients and HIV carriers.
</P>
</TEXT>
