<HEADLINE> Snowstorm Hits Maritime Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Schools were closed in the southeastern part of New Brunswick,
much of mainland Nova Scotia and the entire province of Prince
Edward Island.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of local school kids had to stay dry at home as a
result, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
At least 5,000 residents were left without power in Nova Scotia,
where the Halifax International Airport was closed until 1:00 p.m.
local time.
</P>
<P>
The snowfall later turned into rain of 20 millimeters driven by
winds at 40 to 70 kilometers an hour, said the reports. 
